Hello,

I&#39;m not sure if I understand what exactly is your problem, but it 
seems that you have exactly the same requirement I do. I need to 
start a server, on a separate JVM, start a client, run a suite of 
tests and then shutdown down them all.

I achieved this using both the &lt;parallel&gt; task and the &quot;fork&quot; 
attribute of the &lt;java&gt; task. Following is the code I&#39;m using, please 
consider if it can be of any help.

&lt;target name=&quot;junit&quot; depends=&quot;compile&quot;&gt;
  &lt;parallel&gt;
    &lt;sequential&gt;
      &lt;echo&gt; # Starting Server...&lt;/echo&gt;
      &lt;java dir=&quot;${SERVER_DIR}&quot; classname=&quot;mypackage.MyServer&quot; 
fork=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
        &lt;jvmarg value=&quot;-server&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;classpath refid=&quot;server.classpath&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/java&gt;
    &lt;/sequential&gt;
    &lt;sequential&gt;
      &lt;!-- Waits for the server listener to be up --&gt;
      &lt;waitfor maxwait=&quot;5&quot; maxwaitunit=&quot;second&quot;&gt;
	&lt;socket server=&quot;${server}&quot; port=&quot;${rmiport}&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/waitfor&gt;
      &lt;junit printsummary=&quot;on&quot; fork=&quot;false&quot; haltonfailure=&quot;false&quot;  
failureproperty=&quot;tests.failed&quot; showoutput=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
        &lt;classpath refid=&quot;project.classpath&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;formatter type=&quot;brief&quot; usefile=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;test name=&quot;${testfile}&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/junit&gt;
      &lt;fail if=&quot;tests.failed&quot;&gt;
        *****************************
	One or more tests failed. Check output...
        *****************************
      &lt;/fail&gt;
      &lt;echo&gt;Testes completed.&lt;/echo&gt;
    &lt;/sequential&gt;
  &lt;/parallel&gt;
&lt;/target&gt;

Take care,
Leonardo Barros

